7. Technical Lemmas and Estimates

7.1 Key Estimates

Haar Measure Moments:

\int dU \ U_{ij} U^\dagger_{kl} = \frac{1}{N} \delta_{il} \delta_{jk}

\int dU \ U_{i_1j_1} \cdots U_{i_nj_n} U^\dagger_{k_1l_1} \cdots U^\dagger_{k_nl_n} = \frac{1}{n!} \sum_{\sigma,\tau \in S_n} \delta_{i_1 k_{\sigma(1)}} \cdots \delta_{j_1 l_{\tau(1)}} \cdots

Character Expansion Coefficients:
For SU(N):

c_r(\beta) = \frac{1}{d_r} \int dU \ \chi_r(U) e^{\beta \text{Re tr } U} = I_r(\beta)/I_0(\beta)

with  I_r  modified Bessel functions.

Cluster Expansion Convergence:

\sum_{\Gamma \ni 0} |\zeta(\Gamma)| e^{\kappa |\Gamma|} \leq K(\beta)

Converges for  \beta < \beta_0  with  \beta_0 \approx 0.1  for SU(3).

7.2 Renormalization Constants

One-loop Results:

Z_A = 1 + \frac{g^2}{(4\pi)^2} \left( \frac{11}{3}N \right) \frac{1}{\epsilon} + \cdots

Z_g = 1 - \frac{g^2}{(4\pi)^2} \left( \frac{11}{3}N \right) \frac{1}{2\epsilon} + \cdots

Beta function:

\beta(g) = -\epsilon g - \frac{g^3}{(4\pi)^2} \left( \frac{11}{3}N \right) + O(g^5)

